Western Cape police have on Sunday confirmed that a 40-year-old man has been arrested for the murder of three-year-old Courtney Pieters.The suspect was arrested in Saturn Close, Elsies River, on Sunday, Captain FC van Wyk said in a statement.Pieters&#8217; body was found in a shallow grave in the Epping Industrial centre on Saturday afternoon after she went missing in front of her home in Elsies River 10 days ago.An autopsy of Pieters&#8217; body still had to be completed to determine the cause of death.Once charged, the suspect is expected to appear in the Goodwood Magistrate&#8217;s Court.-TNA Reporter 